<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Ecology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
Solitary or scattered on ground with humus and debris under 
<taxonomicName family="Fagaceae" genus="Xerocomoideae" lsidName="Xerocomoideae" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
trees, mixed with other broadleaf trees, alt. 200-400 m; June to September; currently only known from southern China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
